<Base title="Dunhuang Within Editorial Team" description="Meet the editorial approach behind Dunhuang Within's cultural research, modern spiritual reflections and responsibly described jewelry guides." schema={schema}><article class="article"><nav class="breadcrumbs"><a href="/">Home</a> / Editorial Team</nav><p class="eyebrow">Research · interpretation · responsibility</p><h1>Dunhuang Within Editorial Team</h1><p class="lede">We connect documented Dunhuang culture with contemporary reflection without presenting modern interpretations as ancient teachings.</p><h2>What we cover</h2><p>Our work focuses on Dunhuang history, Mogao art, manuscripts, symbols, reflective practices and the responsible translation of cultural sources into contemporary jewelry and objects of intention.</p><h2>How we work</h2><ol><li>Begin with identifiable primary or institutional sources where available.</li><li>Separate historical context from our contemporary reflection.</li><li>Describe spiritual practices as invitations, not guaranteed outcomes.</li><li>Disclose the limits of medical, supernatural and blessing claims.</li><li>Update pages when sources, products or operational information change.</li></ol><h2>Commercial independence and product standards</h2><p>Dunhuang Within intends to sell jewelry and crystals. That commercial relationship is stated openly. Cultural explanations are not proof that a product has healing powers. Future product pages will disclose materials, makers, sources and design relationships.</p><p>Read our <a href="/editorial-principles/">editorial principles</a> and <a href="/sources-and-methodology/">sources and methodology</a>.</p></article></Base>
